# BookApp

BookApp is a React Native mobile application designed to provide users with a seamless experience for exploring, reading, and managing their favorite books. This app utilizes Firebase for authentication and data management, along with various React Native libraries to enhance performance and UI/UX.

## Features

- Browse and explore books by genre
- View book details, including summaries, author info, and user statistics
- Add books to a personalized library
- Swipe through featured books using an interactive carousel
- Firebase authentication for secure user login
- Offline support with Firestore caching

## Installation

### Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following installed:

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (version >= 18)
- [React Native CLI](https://reactnative.dev/docs/environment-setup)
- Android Studio (for Android development) or Xcode (for iOS development)

### Clone the Repository

```sh
git clone https://github.com/Alex666777666/BookApp.git
cd BookApp
```

### Install Dependencies

```sh
npm install
```

## Running the Application

### Start Metro Bundler

```sh
npm start
```

### Run on Android Emulator/Device

```sh
npm run android
```

### Run on iOS Simulator/Device

```sh
npm run ios
```

(Note: For iOS, ensure you have CocoaPods installed and run `cd ios && pod install` before running the app.)

## Project Structure

```
BookApp/
│-- android/              # Android-specific files
│-- ios/                  # iOS-specific files
│-- src/                  # Main application source code
│   ├── api/              # API service calls
│   ├── assets/           # All UI images or backgrounds
│   ├── components/       # Reusable UI components
│   ├── context/          # Context providers
│   ├── screens/          # Screen components
│   ├── types/            # TypeScript interfaces
│   ├── ui/               # Ui components
│-- App.tsx               # Entry point of the application
│-- package.json          # Project metadata and dependencies
│-- README.md             # Documentation
```

## Dependencies

This project uses the following dependencies:

### Core Dependencies

- React Native (`react-native@0.77.0`)
- React (`react@18.3.1`)
- React Navigation (`@react-navigation/native`, `@react-navigation/native-stack`)
- Firebase (`@react-native-firebase/app`, `@react-native-firebase/auth`, `@react-native-firebase/firestore`)
- React Native Gesture Handler (`react-native-gesture-handler`)
- React Native Reanimated (`react-native-reanimated`)
- React Native Fast Image (`react-native-fast-image`)

### Development Dependencies

- TypeScript (`typescript@5.0.4`)
- Prettier (`prettier@2.8.8`)
